-By who?

14:32.580 --> 14:37.043
Lord Farquaad. He ???

14:39.504 --> 14:40.838
All right.

14:41.088 --> 14:46.302
Who knows where this Farquaad guy is?

14:46.552 --> 14:48.554
Oh I do. I know where he is.

14:48.804 --> 14:53.809
Does anyone else know where to find him?

14:54.060 --> 14:56.604
-Anyone at all? -Me. -Anyone?

14:56.854 --> 15:00.650
Oh pick me, I know! Me, me.

15:00.900 --> 15:03.236
Ok, fine.

15:03.486 --> 15:08.366
Attention all fairy tale things!

15:08.616 --> 15:12.411
Do not get comfortable.
Your welcome is officially warned up.

15:12.662 --> 15:23.256
In fact. I'm gonna see this guy Farquaad right now
and get all off my land and back where you came from.

15:29.095 --> 15:33.057
You. You're coming with me.

15:33.307 --> 15:34.475
All right. That's what I like to hear, man.

15:34.725 --> 15:40.565
Shrek and Donkey, two stubborn friends off on a
world and big city adventure. I love it.

15:40.815 --> 15:46.195
I'm on road again. Sing with me Shrek!
I'm on road again...

15:46.445 --> 15:48.573
What did I say about singing?

15:48.823 --> 15:49.699
-Can I whistle?
-No.

15:49.949 --> 15:55.037
-Well, can I hummer?
-All right.

16:22.523 --> 16:28.529
That's enough. He's ready to talk.

16:38.915 --> 16:42.418
Run, run, run as fast as you can,
you can't catch me.

16:42.668 --> 16:44.837
I'm the gingerbread man.

16:45.087 --> 16:46.297
You monster.

16:46.547 --> 16:48.132
I'm not a monster here. You are.

16:48.382 --> 16:52.887
You and the rest of that fairytale trash,
poisoning my perfect world.

16:53.137 --> 16:57.391
-Now tell me! Where are the others?
-Eat me.

16:57.642 --> 17:02.188
I've tried to be fair to you, creatures.
Now my patience has reached its end!

17:02.438 --> 17:05.148
-Tell me! Or I'll...
-No, no, not the buttons.

17:05.398 --> 17:07.108
Not gumdrop buttons.

17:07.359 --> 17:09.278
All right! Who's hiding them?

17:09.529 --> 17:11.781
Ok, I'll tell you.

17:12.031 --> 17:15.076
-Do you know the muffin-man?
-The muffin-man?

17:15.326 --> 17:18.746
-The muffin-man.
-Yes, I know the muffin-man.

17:18.996 --> 17:20.705
Who lives on Proully lane?

17:20.957 --> 17:24.417
-Well, she's married to the muffin-man.
-The muffin-man!

17:24.669 --> 17:28.840
-The muffin-man!
-She's married to the muffin-man.

17:29.090 --> 17:31.050
My lord! We found it.

17:31.300 --> 17:36.889
Well then, what are you waiting for?
Bring it in.

17:48.818 --> 17:50.319
Magic mirror.

17:50.570 --> 17:55.616
Don't tell him anything!

17:56.742 --> 17:58.578
Evening.

17:58.828 --> 18:04.083
Mirror, mirror on the wall.
Is this not the most perfect kingdom of them all?

18:04.333 --> 18:07.378
Well, technically, you're not a king.

18:07.628 --> 18:10.089
A..., felonious.

18:10.339 --> 18:12.133
-You were saying.
-What I mean is a...

18:12.383 --> 18:13.593
...you're not a king, yet.

18:13.843 --> 18:18.598
But you can become one.
All you have to do, is marry a princess.

18:18.848 --> 18:20.766
Go on.

18:21.017 --> 18:23.978
So, just sit back and relax my lord,

18:24.228 --> 18:29.066
because it's time for you
to meet today's eligible bachelorettes.

18:29.317 --> 18:32.320
And here they are.

18:32.570 --> 18:36.949
Bachelorette number one is a mentally abused
shading from a kingdom far, far away.

18:37.200 --> 18:39.619
She likes sushi and hottubbing anytime.

18:39.869 --> 18:43.080
